data.chText: 聚集；集合；收集
data.enText: to come together as a group; to bring people or things together as a group

data.chText: 全体学生获通知到大礼堂集合。
data.enText: All the students were asked to assemble in the main hall.

data.chText: 接着她向全体集合者讲话。
data.enText: She then addressed the assembled company (= all the people there) .

data.chText: 收集证据 / 数据
data.enText: to assemble evidence/data

data.chText: 经理已聚集了一个世界一流的班子。
data.enText: The manager has assembled a world-class team.

data.chText: 装配；组装
data.enText: to fit together all the separate parts of sth, for example a piece of furniture

data.chText: 搁架容易装配。
data.enText: The shelves are easy to assemble.

data.text: build ♦ construct ♦ assemble ♦ erect ♦ set up ♦ put up ♦ put together

data.chText: 以上各词均含制造、建造之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to make sth, especially by putting different parts together.
build

data.chText: 指制造、建造、修建（尤指房屋）：
data.enText: to make sth, especially a building, by putting parts together

data.chText: 用石头建造的房子
data.enText: a house built of stone

data.chText: 他们要在老发电站那里盖房子。
data.enText: They're going to build on the site of the old power station.
construct

data.chText: 指修建、建造（公路、房屋、机器等）
data.enText: [often passive] ( rather formal ) to build sth such as a road, building or machine
assemble

data.chText: 指装配、组装（家具、机器等）：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to fit together all the separate parts of sth such as a piece of furniture or a machine

data.chText: 这个橱柜容易组装。
data.enText: The cupboard is easy to assemble.
erect

data.chText: 指建立、建造、安装、竖立、搭起：
data.enText: ( formal ) to build sth; to put sth in position and make it stand upright

data.chText: 警察只得设立路障来阻截人群。
data.enText: Police had to erect barriers to keep crowds back.
set sth up

data.chText: 指搭建、建立、设立、设置：
data.enText: to build sth or place sth somewhere

data.chText: 我们决定搭帐篷过夜。
data.enText: We decided to set up camp for the night.
put sth up

data.chText: 指修建、建立、设立、设置：
data.enText: to build sth or place sth somewhere

data.chText: 他们正在盖新旅馆以促进该地区的旅游业。
data.enText: They're putting up new hotels in order to boost tourism in the area.

data.chText: 用set sth up还是put sth up？
set sth up不用于永久性的建筑：
data.enText: Set sth up is not used for permanent buildings.
They're setting up new hotels.

data.chText: 搭帐篷用set up camp或put up a tent。搭建其他临时建筑用set up或put up均可：
data.enText: You set up camp but put up a tent . For other temporary structures you can use either word.

data.chText: 架篱笆；设屏障；搭棚子
data.enText: to set up/put up a fence/barrier/shelter
set sth up or put sth up?
put sth together

data.chText: 指组装、组织、汇集：
data.enText: to make or prepare sth by fitting or collecting parts together

data.chText: 组装飞机模型
data.enText: to put together a model plane
to build/construct/erect/put up a house/bridge/wall
to build/construct/erect/put up some shelves
to build/construct/erect/put up a barrier/fence/shelter
to build/construct/assemble/put together a(n) engine/machine
to build/construct a road/railway/railroad/tunnel
to erect/put up a tent/statue/monument
to assemble/put together the parts/sections of sth

simple_means.memory_skill: as 加强 + sembl 相类似，一样 + e → 不断集合类似的东西 → 集合

ex.chText: 男生和女生集合起来去野餐。
ex.enText: The boys and girls gathered for a picnic.

ex.chText: 出事地点聚集了一群人。
ex.enText: A crowd gathered at the scene of the accident.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指人和物，侧重于围绕某个中心而聚集。

ex.chText: 一大群人聚集在办公大楼前面。
ex.enText: A large crowd assembled in front of the office building.

ex.chText: 她收集了一些自己最喜欢的专辑。
ex.enText: She has assembled a collection of her favourite albums.

synonyms.bx: 常指为某种目的聚集在一起。

ex.chText: 人群开始聚集在事故现场。
ex.enText: A crowd was starting to collect around the spot of the accident.

ex.chText: 越来越多的人开始聚集在大使馆前面。
ex.enText: More and more people began to collect in front of the embassy.

synonyms.bx: 指人在某一处集中或逐渐地聚集成群。

ex.chText: 教学小组每周开会一次。
ex.enText: The teaching group convenes every week.

ex.chText: 总统召集部长（开会）讨论这个问题。
ex.enText: The president convened (a meeting of) his ministers to discuss the matter.

synonyms.bx: 指聚集起来或召集有关人员举行正式会议。

tr: create by putting components or members together

example: We assembled in the church basement
Let's gather in the dining room
get together all those who are interested in the project

value.def: When people assemble or when someone assembles them, they come together in a group, usually for a particular purpose such as a meeting.

example.ex: There wasn't even a convenient place for students to assemble between classes...
example.tran: 在课间，学生们连一个方便凑在一起的地方都没有。

example.ex: Thousands of people, mainly Zulus, assembled in a stadium in Thokoza...
example.tran: 数以千计的人，主要是祖鲁族人，聚集在托考查的一个体育场里。

example.ex: He has assembled a team of experts to handle queries...
example.tran: 他召集了一班专家来答疑解惑。

example.ex: The assembled multitude cheered and whistled as the political leaders arrived.
example.tran: 当政治领袖到达的时候，聚集的人群欢呼起来,并吹起了口哨。

value.def: To assemble something means to collect it together or to fit the different parts of it together.

example.ex: Greenpeace managed to assemble enough boats to waylay the ship at sea...
example.tran: 绿色和平组织设法聚集起足够数量的小船在海上拦截该船。

example.ex: She had been trying to assemble the bomb when it went off in her arms...
example.tran: 在她试图组装炸弹时，炸弹在她怀里爆炸了。

example.ex: He is assembling evidence concerning a murder.
example.tran: 他正在收集一桩谋杀案的证据。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = alike, same 相类似, 一样
rootsaffixes.title: simil, simul(t), sembl

partsOfSpeech.dec: as 加强 + sembl 相类似，一样 + e → 不断集合类似的东西 → 集合
as 加强 + simil 相类似，一样 + ate 使… → 使成为一样 → 同化
dis 不 + sembl 相类似，一样 + e → 不相同〔装做相同〕→ 假装
dis 不 + similar 同样的；相似的 → 不同的
dis 不 + simil 相类似，一样 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 使不一样 → 异化
fac 做 + simil 相类似，一样 + e → 做得跟真的一样 → 誊写
re 一再 + sembl 相类似，一样 + ance 状态，性质，状况 → 类似
re 一再 + sembl 相类似，一样 + e → 再怎么都一样 → 类似
sembl 相类似，一样 + ance 表状态 →〔外观〕相同之处 → 类似
simil 相类似，一样 + ar …的 → 同样的；相似的
similar 同样的；相似的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 类似
simil 相类似，一样 + e → 像…一样 → 明喻
simil 相类似，一样 + itude 表状态 → 类似
simul 相类似，一样 + ate 做 → 做得像真的 → 模仿
simul 相类似，一样 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 假装
simult 相类似，一样 + aneous 有…特征的 →〔时间〕相同的 → 同时发生的
simult 相类似，一样 + aneity 表性质 → 同时性
veri〔= ver 真实的〕+ simil 相类似，一样 + ar …的 → 像真的一样 → 貌似真实的
